    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** offense is well-positioned for today's slate, headlined by the elite efficiency of **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29). Facing Wacha, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 15% SP skill boost and favorable wind conditions, making him the anchor of our lineup at the top of the order. **Kyle Tucker** (77.88) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) follow closely in projected value; **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** thrives against Fuentes, where an assumption of a #2 spot coupled with a 19% SP skill advantage creates an ideal environment for Roto production. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) draws an exceptional matchup against Sugano, with a 14% park factor boost and 17% SP skill advantage driving his high efficiency as a cornerstone in the outfield.\n\nPlatoon edges are the primary catalyst for today\u2019s aggressive lineup configuration. We are leaning heavily into the matchup against Fuentes, starting **Nasim Nunez** (68.23) and **Brady House** (63.81) to capitalize on the 5.07 xERA baseline. **Luis Robert Jr.** (66.04) remains a strong play despite a sub-optimal park factor, as his 14% platoon edge against a lefty keeps his floor well above the 60 threshold. The most difficult decision rested with **Marcell Ozuna** (60.82), who narrowly missed the starting cut; while his baseline is solid, the optimizer favored **Miguel Vargas** (61.70) due to a higher projected order position and superior tactical placement against Rodriguez. \n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for several key contributors. Should **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Brady House**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, or **Miguel Vargas** slide down their respective batting orders, their daily efficiency scores will contract accordingly. Furthermore, while **Liam Hicks** (46.57) provides adequate coverage at C1, the matchup against Leahy lacks the offensive upside found elsewhere. We are carrying **Nolan Schanuel**, **Coby Mayo**, **Josh Jung**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Heliot Ramos**, and **Dominic Smith** on the bench; these players, along with **Marcell Ozuna**, are prepared to rotate in should any of our starters be scratched or suffer a late-hour decline in matchup security.",
